snippet: For the past seven years, the Dogs have handily outperformed the Dow itself and other benchmarks of blue-chip stocks.
lead_paragraph: EVERY dog has its day, but the Dogs of the Dow have had their day for seven years. During that span, the Dogs  the 10 stocks in the Dow Jones industrial average with the highest dividend yields at the end of each year  have handily outperformed the index itself and other benchmarks of blue-chip stocks.

headline.main: Dow’s Dogs Still Having Their Day
